The paper deals with the problem of ranking archived documents for structured queries on semantic layers, which involves combining metadata and content-based semantic information. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), deep learning (cs.DL), databases (cs.DB), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, given that the paper focuses on the use of semantic layers and semantic query languages, it is most likely to be classified under cs.IR.
